



git --version

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com"

git config --global --list
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "youremail@example.com"
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub

--> Add SSH key to GitHub
Go to GitHub → Settings → SSH and GPG keys
Click New SSH key
Paste the key
Give it a name (e.g. “RStudio Server”)
Save

ssh -T git@github.com

Create repository in Github & copy
git@github.com:danakrs/scRNASeq_Krauss_etal_2025.git

In RStudio empty project folder git init

Created RProject
Edit .gitignore


Locally:
git status
git add .
git commit -m "Initial project structure"


git remote add origin git@github.com:danakrs/scRNASeq_Krauss_etal_2025.git
git remote -v # check

git branch -M main
git push -u origin main




Then daily workflow
git status
git add .
git commit -m "Meaningful message"
git push

git pull # to get updates



